rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
An ethnicity or ethnic group is a group of individuals that share common characteristics, such as ancestry, country of origin, language, religion, culture, and physical appearance.
Things that are ethnicities:
## Ancestry (e.g. Jews).
## Nationality or Country of origin (e.g. Italian, German, Filipino).
## Groups based on skin color (e.g. Black, White).
## Groups based on language (e.g. Hispanic).
## Groups based on continent (e.g. Asian, European, African).
## Groups based on combinations of the above (e.g. Japanese American, German Canadian).
## Minorities, indigenous peoples, and tribes(e.g. Bundjalung people, Cheyenne, Hadza, Layap, Rio Pardo).
Things that are NOT ethnicities:
## Organizations (e.g. Indigenous Peoples of Africa Co-ordinating Committee).
## Clans (e.g. Reer Guled, Bharwana).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ethnicity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Languages that are associated with the given ethnicity, e.g. the Farsi language is associated with the Iranian ethnicity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Locations that are associated with the given ethnicity, e.g. Spain and parts of Latin America are associated with the Hispanic ethnicity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An ethnicity that subsumes the given ethnicity. For example, the Torbesh ethnicity is included in the Slavic ethnicity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Ethnicity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of people around the world that are part of the given ethnicity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Population

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A group of people that are related to one another either genetically or by marriage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person who founded the family or who is responsible for the notoriety of the family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Founder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person who is part of the given family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Member

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a family to the name of the family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Name

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The period (such as the 18th Century or the Renaissance) during which or the event because of which the family became famous or notorious.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rise to prominence
Family name

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.kinship_relationship to the object of the kinship relation. The type of kinship is dependent on the person in the subject of the relationship. For example, if 'Chelsea Clinton' is the subject of the relation and 'Hillary Clinton' is the object, then 'Daughter' is the type of kinship. Conversely, if 'Hillary Clinton' is the subject and 'Chelsea Clinton' the object, then the type of kinship is 'Mother'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Object

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.kinship_relationship to the object of the kinship relation. The type of kinship is dependent on the person in the subject of the relationship. For example, if 'Chelsea Clinton' is the subject of the relation and 'Hillary Clinton' is the object, then 'Daughter' is the type of kinship. Conversely, if 'Hillary Clinton' is the subject and 'Chelsea Clinton' the object, then the type of kinship is 'Mother'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A person is a human being (man, woman or child) known to have actually existed. Living persons, celebrities, and politicians are persons, as are deceased persons.
Things that are persons;
## Living persons, celebrities, politicians, etc. (e.g. Jeff Kinney, Julia Roberts, Barack Obama).
## Deceased persons and historical persons (e.g. Anne Frank, Henry VIII of England, Brittany Murphy). These should be assigned to the subtype mso:people.deceased_person.
Things that are NOT persons:
## Groups of people like twins, duos, couples (e.g. Bob and Mike Bryan, the Wayans brothers, Brangelina).
## Professions, ranks and titles. Use mso:people.profession for people's professions (e.g. nurse).
## Fictional, mythical, and legendary agents (e.g. Sookie Stackhouse, Han Solo, Finn Hudson). In these cases use mso:fictional_universe.character.
## Deities and gods. Use mso:religion.deity for these.
## The representation of a real person in fiction. In these cases, use mso:fictional_universe.character. The character should then be linked to the corresponding instance of mso:people.person by the property mso:fictional_universe.character.based_on. See, for example, Henry V of England (the real person) and Henry V (the representation of the real person in fiction).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a profession to a profession's share of employment in a given area relative to the profession's share of employment in the country as a whole . Note that the given area is specified with the property mso:measurement_unit.dated_value.location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location Quotient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a profession to the average number of job openings in the profession per year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Openings Yearly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.profession to the average hourly pay for the profession over a given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Pay Hourly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.profession to the average annual pay for the profession over a given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mean Pay Yearly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.profession to its hourly median pay for a given time period. For example, the hourly median pay for software developers in 2012 was $44.88.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hourly Median Pay

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.profession to its yearly median pay for a given time period. For example, the yearly median pay for software developers in 2012 was $93,350.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yearly Median Pay

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.profession to the description of the post-employment training needed to gain competency in the skills needed for the given profession.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Required On-the-job Training

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The general discipline that is related to the given profession, e.g. the relationship between software testing and software engineering.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Profession

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A trade union that represents the given profession.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trade Union

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:people.profession to the description of work experience commonly considered needed by employers or that is an acceptable substitute for formal types of training or education for the given profession.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Work Experience in a Related Occuption
Professional field
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There is no clear distinction between a 'profession' and a 'professional field'. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:people.profession]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that stores information about people's romantic relationships, when and where they began, if and when they ended, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Romantic relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of intimate relationship between two people, e.g. dated, slept with, engaged to, etc. The value for this property should be the one that expresses the greatest degree of involvement. For example, if the couple both dated and slept together, the value 'dated' should be used, which (at least in the celebrity world) means the couple also slept together.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relationship type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of intimate relationship between two people, e.g. dated, slept with, engaged to, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Romantic relationship type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship representing salary data for a person and another agent paying the salary.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Salary Relationship
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. Use business.employment_tenure instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:business.employment_tenure]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a salary relationship to the person being paid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person Paid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a salary relationship to the salary.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Salary

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a salary relationship to the payer of the salary. Note that both organizations and individual people, among other agents, can be payers of salaries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Salary Payer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The sexual orientation of the person, whether gay, heterosexual or bisexual.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sexual orientation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sexual orientation, e.g. gay, heterosexual or bisexual, to a person who has the sexual orientation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sexual Orientation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type which allows a person to be related to information about their sexual orientation and the time frame(s) when they had the given orientation.
The date that the sexual orientation phase of the person ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The sexual orientation of the person, whether gay, heterosexual or bisexual.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the sexual orientation of the person during the given phase.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sexual Orientation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that the sexual orientation phase of the person began.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start
